# 07.02 User Problems

## Overview

The User Problems document defines the main challenges that cmdOS is designed to solve.

Traditional computing systems require users to understand applications, interfaces, workflows, and technical processes.

cmdOS changes this model by allowing users to communicate their goals naturally and allowing AI Agents to execute tasks on their behalf.

Core principle:

User Problem

↓

AI Understanding

↓

Automated Solution

↓

Execution

---

# 1. Problem Definition

Modern digital systems have become increasingly powerful but also increasingly complex.

Users must manage:

- Many applications
- Multiple accounts
- Different workflows
- Complex interfaces
- Technical processes

The problem is not lack of computing power.

The problem is the complexity of controlling computers.

---

# 2. Application Complexity Problem

## Current Situation

Traditional systems require users to manually find and operate applications.

Example:

User wants to organize a business trip.

Current workflow:

Open browser

↓

Search flights

↓

Compare options

↓

Open hotel applications

↓

Check calendar

↓

Send information

↓

Manage documents

---

## cmdOS Solution

User:

"Plan my business trip to Tokyo next week."

cmdOS:

- Understands the objective
- Searches options
- Creates a plan
- Requests permission
- Executes actions

